无动于衷
doin' nothin' about it.

183
00:10:46,410 --> 00:10:50,170
无动于衷和耐心等待 是有区别的
There's a difference between doing nothing and waiting.

184
00:10:50,870 --> 00:10:52,330
那我们在等什么?
So what are we waiting for?

185
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:57,970
你们回岛上来的唯一条件
You were only able to come back to this island

186
00:10:58,160 --> 00:10:59,740
就是所有人同心协力
because you all did it together.

187
00:11:00,450 --> 00:11:01,990
如果我们想登机离开
If we're gonna get on that plane and leave,

188
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:03,740
也必须这样做
it has to happen the same way.

189
00:11:04,740 --> 00:11:06,800
我们等其他朋友来这儿回合 Kate...
We're waiting for your friends to get here, Kate...

190
00:11:06,990 --> 00:11:09,550
比如Hugo Sun Jack...
Hugo, Sun, Jack...

191
00:11:10,390 --> 00:11:11,220
只有这样
That's the only way

192
00:11:11,410 --> 00:11:15,230
我们才能离开这个荒岛
we're ever getting off this godforsaken rock.

193
00:11:15,660 --> 00:11:18,550
- 我可不看好这事  - 那我们走着瞧吧
- Well, I don't see that happening.  - Well, let's just hope you're wrong.

194
00:11:30,220 --> 00:11:32,180
你去哪儿了?
Where you been?

195
00:11:33,350 --> 00:11:35,040
我能单独和你谈谈么?
Can I speak to you in private?

196
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,590
当然可以
Absolutely.

197
00:11:53,580 --> 00:11:54,940
一切顺利吧?
Everything go all right?

198
00:11:55,160 --> 00:11:56,460
嗯
Yes.

199
00:11:56,670 --> 00:11:57,930
Widmore见了你?
Did Widmore see you?

200
00:11:58,350 --> 00:12:01,280
- 没 但他手下见了  - 你没杀掉他们?
- No, but his people did.  - And you let them live?

201
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:02,490
我没有杀他们的理由
I didn't see the point of killing them

202
00:12:02,650 --> 00:12:06,070
- 毕竟我有事在身  - 那你弄清楚了他们藏在潜水艇上的东西 是什么吗?
- when I had what I came for.  - So you found what they were hiding in the submarine?

203
00:12:07,460 --> 00:12:09,170
一清二楚
I most certainly did.

204
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:56,270
现在怎么办?
Now what?

205
00:12:58,020 --> 00:13:00,460
我们得去多找些炸药 否则她就死得没意义了
We get more dynamite or else she died for nothing.

206
00:13:00,620 --> 00:13:03,190
或许她的死 就是在暗示我们 别碰那些该死的炸药
Maybe she died to show us to stay the hell away from dynamite.

207
00:13:03,340 --> 00:13:05,320
Jack 我倒乐意冒一冒这个险
Well, Jack, that's a risk I'm willing to take.

208
00:13:05,490 --> 00:13:08,510
Richard 我答应过要带她离岛的
Richard, I promised I'd get her off this island.

209
00:13:08,710 --> 00:13:10,450
Jack 我... 我希望你别这么做
Well, Jack, I... I wish you hadn't done that.

210
00:13:10,970 --> 00:13:14,400
- 如果这样能让你好受些的话 你可以把责任全推到我身上  - 我认为Richard是对的
- If it makes you feel any better, you can blame it on me.  - I think Richard's right.

211
00:13:19,450 --> 00:13:20,990
这是我们唯一的选择
It's the only choice we've got.

212
00:13:24,590 --> 00:13:25,990
相信我 Jack
Trust me, Jack.

213
00:13:31,310 --> 00:13:32,410
好吧
Okay.

214
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:34,590
好 我们走
Good. Let's get moving.

215
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:43,120
38号? 38号在吗?
38? Number 38?

216
00:13:45,590 --> 00:13:47,100
Reyes先生!
Mr. Reyes!

217
00:13:47,280 --> 00:13:48,270
真是太荣幸了
What an honor.

218
00:13:48,460 --> 00:13:50,770
给我一个全家桶
Give me a bucket, family size.

219
00:13:50,980 --> 00:13:54,280
没问题 马上就好 先生
Of course. Right away, sir.

220
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:55,990
41号?
41?

221
00:13:56,140 --> 00:13:57,730
41号在吗?
Number 41?

222
00:14:04,900 --> 00:14:06,460
看什么看?
What?

223
00:14:10,970 --> 00:14:12,310
抱歉
I'm sorry.

224
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:15,170
我们以前见过吗?
Have I seen you before?

225
00:14:15,350 --> 00:14:17,650
我是这儿的老板 可能你看过我的广告吧
I own the place. Maybe you saw my commercial.

226
00:14:17,810 --> 00:14:19,670
莫非你想要一个"咯咯鸡"钥匙扣?
You want a clucketeer keychain?

227
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:21,700
不... 不 不是说那个
N... no. It's not that.

228
00:14:24,690 --> 00:14:27,060
你坐过大洋航空的815次航班吗?
Were you on Oceanic flight 815?

229
00:14:27,260 --> 00:14:29,810
- 大概一星期前 从悉尼来的那个?  - 呃 没错
- A bout a week ago, from Sydney?  - Uh, yeah.

230
00:14:30,450 --> 00:14:32,760
- 我也是  - 哇 真巧啊
- So was I.  - Wow. What a coincidence.

231
00:14:33,070 --> 00:14:35,510
是啊 反正我也在等着叫号 介意我跟你坐一会儿吗?
Yeah. Listen, you mind if I join you while I wait for my order?

232
00:14:37,690 --> 00:14:39,080
请吧
Be my guest.

233
00:14:39,300 --> 00:14:40,920
哦 好多鸡啊
Ooh. That is a lot of chicken.

234
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:44,940
- 每当沮丧的时候 我就狂吃一顿  - 啊 她叫什么名字?
- I eat when I'm depressed.  - Ah. So what's her name?

235
00:14:46,890 --> 00:14:48,930
前两天我相亲的时候 遇到了一个姑娘
I met a girl on a blind date the other night.

236
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:50,970
是不是... 是不是与你想象的大相径庭?
And you didn't...  It didn't go how you'd hoped?

237
00:14:51,190 --> 00:14:53,260
她美若天仙
She was totally awesome,

238
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:55,590
除了一点以外... 她疯了
expect for one thing...  she's crazy.

239
00:14:57,370 --> 00:14:59,230
哥们 所有女人都有点疯狂的
Well, all women are a little bit crazy, brother.

240
00:14:59,410 --> 00:15:02,940
不 她是真的疯
No. This one actually lives in the looney bin.

241
00:15:03,180 --> 00:15:05,870
我看到了那个面包车 上面全是疯子
I mean, I saw the van. She's full-on nuts.

242
00:15:06,100 --> 00:15:08,020
她才清醒了点儿
I mean, she started sane,

243
00:15:08,210 --> 00:15:10,540
但紧接着 她就对我说 我们以前就认识...
but then she told me that we already knew each other...

244
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:13,140
至于这事么? 我有同感
And that? I'd remember.

245
00:15:15,960 --> 00:15:17,340
跟我说说...
Tell me something...

246
00:15:18,820 --> 00:15:20,730
她说她认识你的时候 你相信她吗?
Did you believe her when she said she knew you?

247
00:15:24,300 --> 00:15:25,710
是的
Yeah.

248
00:15:27,150 --> 00:15:28,520
有一点吧
Kinda.

249
00:15:29,620 --> 00:15:31,590
你得跟着感觉走
You know, I say go with your gut.

250
00:15:33,300 --> 00:15:34,980
或许你应该...
You know, maybe you should...

251
00:15:35,580 --> 00:15:38,360
在对她绝望之前 你应该找到
you should try to find out where she thinks she knew you from

252
00:15:39,780 --> 00:15:41,770
你们相识的那个地方
before you give up on her.

253
00:15:43,930 --> 00:15:46,570
42号? 42号在吗?
42? Order 42?

254
00:15:46,990 --> 00:15:48,750
啊 到我了 哥们
Ah, that's me, brother.

255
00:15:52,720 --> 00:15:54,380
很高兴碰到你
It was nice bumping into you.

256
00:16:05,110 --> 00:16:06,380
你好
Hello.

257
00:16:06,720 --> 00:16:07,560
你好
Hello.

258
00:16:07,750 --> 00:16:09,180
很抱歉Sayid把你绑了起来
I'm sorry Sayid tied you up,

259
00:16:09,350 --> 00:16:13,220
- 他是怕 你在我们交谈之前就跑了  - 我不怪他
- But he was afraid you'd run before we had a chance to talk.  - I don't blame him.

260
00:16:13,420 --> 00:16:15,150
虽然在他离开之前 我已经解释过了
Although as I explained to him before he left,

261
00:16:16,990 --> 00:16:18,820
我无处可逃啊 哥们
I have nowhere to run to, brother.

262
00:16:21,520 --> 00:16:24,190
这大概是我所听过的
Well, if that's not the best argument against captivity

263
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:25,760
最佳脱困词了吧
that I've ever heard,

264
00:16:25,920 --> 00:16:27,970
再也找不出比这更好的了
I don't know what is.

265
00:16:37,980 --> 00:16:40,390
我能问你几个问题吗 Desmond?
You mind if I ask you a couple questions, Desmond?

266
00:16:40,980 --> 00:16:42,110
问吧
Not at all.

267
00:16:43,570 --> 00:16:46,130
为什么Charles Widmore把你带回岛上来?
Why did Charles Widmore bring you back to the Island?

268
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:48,940
我是被绑的那个
Considering I was kidnapped,

269
00:16:50,810 --> 00:16:52,280
你还是问他吧
you'd have to ask him.

270
00:16:55,220 --> 00:16:57,130
他们全副武装地带着他
They had him under armed guard.

271
00:16:57,350 --> 00:16:58,790
他把我扔进了一间木屋
He threw me into a wood shack

272
00:16:59,540 --> 00:17:02,410
然后对我进行强力电磁场实验
and blasted me with a massive amount of electromagnetism.

273
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:06,040
希望你不介意我这么问 Desmond
If you don't mind my asking, Desmond,

274
00:17:06,220 --> 00:17:09,870
你怎么知道 他对你做的实验是什么?
how can you be sure what it was that he blasted you with?

275
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:12,210
经验
Experience.

276
00:17:16,410 --> 00:17:18,070
你知道我是谁吗?
Do you know who I am?

277
00:17:18,260 --> 00:17:19,780
当然
Of course.

278
00:17:22,860 --> 00:17:24,440
你是John Locke
You're John Locke.

279
00:17:30,420 --> 00:17:32,350
回到扎营的地方 我马上回来
Head back to camp. I'll be back soon.

280
00:17:32,810 --> 00:17:34,080
你要去哪儿?
Where are you going?

281
00:17:34,280 --> 00:17:36,900
Desmond和我要去散散步
Desmond and I need to take a walk.

282
00:17:43,010 --> 00:17:44,430
我要给你看点东西
Something I'd like to show you.

283
00:17:54,520 --> 00:17:55,850
又让你若有所思了 是吧?
Kinda makes you think, doesn't it?

284
00:17:56,960 --> 00:17:58,150
那是什么?
What's that?

285
00:17:58,340 --> 00:17:59,750
Ilana啊
Ilana.

286
00:18:00,380 --> 00:18:02,110
她就在这儿
There she was,

287
00:18:02,320 --> 00:18:04,370
Jacob挑出来的
Handpicked by Jacob,

288
00:18:05,230 --> 00:18:07,980
专门训练来保护你们这些接班人的
Trained to come and protect you candidates.

289
00:18:09,760 --> 00:18:12,520
一旦她告诉你 你是谁的话
No sooner does she tell you who you are,

290
00:18:14,040 --> 00:18:15,520
她就炸死了
then she blows up.

291
00:18:18,010 --> 00:18:19,880
这座岛就随之玩完了
The Island was done with her.

292
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:24,530
所以我很想知道 如果由我们来做的话 会发生什么事情
Makes me wonder what's gonna happen when it's done with us.

293
00:18:45,100 --> 00:18:47,670
好了 各位 这可能得花几分钟时间
All right, everyone. This might take a few minutes.

294
00:18:48,020 --> 00:18:49,990
除了我以外 我不想让任何人来碰触这些炸药
I don't want anyone but me handling that dynamite,

295
00:18:50,150 --> 00:18:53,020
所以我要一个人进去 Hugo在哪儿?
so I'm gonna go in alone. Where's Hugo?

296
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:56,760
- 我还以为他在你前面  - 快跑!
- I thought he was up front with you.  - Run!

297
00:18:57,950 --> 00:18:59,250
快跑!
Run!

298
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:00,970
快跑啊!
Go! Go! Go! Go!

299
00:19:21,700 --> 00:19:23,490
你干嘛要这么干啊?!
Why the hell did you do that?!

300
00:19:25,920 --> 00:19:27,820
我是在保护大家啊
I'm protecting us.

301
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:33,040
- 你究竟在想什么啊?!  - 冷静点
- What the hell were you thinking?!  - Calm down.

302
00:19:33,210 --> 00:19:35,500
- 现在该怎么办... 现在我们怎么办?  - 别说了 够了
- Now what... what are we supposed to do now?  - That's it. That's enough.

303
00:19:35,680 --> 00:19:36,860
我们死定了 我们都死定了
We're dead. We're all dead.

304
00:19:43,260 --> 00:19:45,580
至少该提前给声警报啊 Hugo
A warning might have been nice there, Hugo.

305
00:19:46,380 --> 00:19:48,500
我说了"跑"的嘛
I did say "run."

306
00:19:50,580 --> 00:19:52,010
为什么你要那么干?
Why'd you do that?

307
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:53,890
Michael让我这么干的
Michael told me to.

308
00:19:54,140 --> 00:19:55,340
谁?
Who?

309
00:19:56,130 --> 00:19:57,340
Michael啊
Michael.

310
00:19:57,530 --> 00:19:58,400
有些死者 会回来冲我大喊大叫
He's one of the people who come back

311
00:19:58,580 --> 00:20:01,110
他就是其中之一
and yell at me after they die.

312
00:20:02,290 --> 00:20:03,630
他让我阻止大家
He told me I had to stop everyone

313
00:20:03,790 --> 00:20:04,750
去炸掉飞机
from blowing up the plane.

314
00:20:04,940 --> 00:20:08,350
所以... 没有炸药了 也就没有爆炸了
So... no dynamite, no more blowing up.

315
00:20:10,060 --> 00:20:11,580
经常发生这事吗
That happen a lot,

316
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:13,450
死人对着你吼叫?
dead people yelling at you?

317
00:20:14,640 --> 00:20:16,030
经常发生
It happens enough.

318
00:20:16,210 --> 00:20:19,250
你就听从他们所说的了?
And you just listen to whatever they say?

319
00:20:20,830 --> 00:20:23,260
死人比活人更可靠
Dead people are more reliable than alive people.

320
00:20:26,710 --> 00:20:28,500
有什么可以帮你的吗 Reyes先生?
How can I help you, Mr. Reyes?

321
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:32,970
我想向你打听一下几天前的那个姑娘
I wanted to ask you about that girl the other day.

322
00:20:33,460 --> 00:20:35,010
叫Libby的那个?
Libby?

323
00:20:35,630 --> 00:20:38,360
我能不能见见她
I was wondering if maybe I could see her.

324
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:41,880
我觉得可能不行
Well, I don't think that's a good idea.

325
00:20:42,290 --> 00:20:43,570
她不太舒服
She's not well.

326
00:20:43,750 --> 00:20:44,890
显然 如果只是去
Clearly, she's well enough

327
00:20:45,030 --> 00:20:48,180
比如... 吃个墨西哥鸡肉卷 她不会有事的
for, like, a... Fajita field trip.

328
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:49,570
那是我的错
Well, that's my mistake.

329
00:20:49,850 --> 00:20:51,850
我对她的情况判断失误了
I misjudged her condition.

330
00:20:53,450 --> 00:20:54,830
她的情况?
Her condition?

331
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:56,920
她认不清现实
She has issues with reality.

332
00:20:57,730 --> 00:20:58,910
你什么意思?
What do you mean?

333
00:20:59,260 --> 00:21:02,330
我只是觉得 你现在见她
I just think it probably wouldn't be a good idea

334
00:21:02,490 --> 00:21:04,310
可能不太妥当
for you to see her right now.

335
00:21:04,920 --> 00:21:06,150
这只会让她更糊涂
It'll only confuse her.

336
00:21:06,330 --> 00:21:07,430
你说了"可能"
You said "probably,"

337
00:21:07,610 --> 00:21:09,590
就是说 可能会有例外喽
which means you might make an exception.

338
00:21:10,430 --> 00:21:11,860
或许家属就没问题吧
Well, perhaps for family.

339
00:21:13,150 --> 00:21:14,690
抑或是一个慷慨的捐赠者?
Or a generous donor?

340
00:21:15,820 --> 00:21:17,240
什么?
I'm sorry?

341
00:21:21,270 --> 00:21:23,790
我进来的时候 发现娱乐室很简陋啊
The rec room looked pretty gnarly on my way in.

342
00:21:24,460 --> 00:21:26,510
你觉得十万块能买些什么呢?
What do you think 100k might buy?

343
00:21:54,290 --> 00:21:56,000
你记起来了?
You remembered?

344
00:21:56,990 --> 00:21:58,550
没有
No.

345
00:21:58,770 --> 00:22:00,320
对不起
I'm sorry.

346
00:22:02,290 --> 00:22:04,420
那你为什么来这儿?
Then why are you here?

347
00:22:07,020 --> 00:22:09,200
你是在什么地方认识我的?
Where is it you think you know me from?

348
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:11,510
呃 我不知道
Um, I'm not sure.

349
00:22:13,470 --> 00:22:15,100
我知道这有点讲不通
I know it won't make sense.

350
00:22:15,100 --> 00:22:16,070
我...
I...

351
00:22:16,310 --> 00:22:17,780
说说看嘛
Try me.

352
00:22:24,080 --> 00:22:26,250
几天前 我正在看电视
A few days ago, I was watching TV,

353
00:22:26,250 --> 00:22:28,660
看到了你的一则广告
and one of your commercials came on.

354
00:22:28,660 --> 00:22:31,200
就在我看到你的那一瞬间
And the moment that I saw you,

355
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:33,070
我的脑袋就像是被敲了一下
It was like I was hit over the head.

356
00:22:33,070 --> 00:22:35,360
我生活中的所有这些回忆
All these memories

357
00:22:35,360 --> 00:22:38,120
一下次全涌现出来了...
came washing back... of my life,

358
00:22:38,120 --> 00:22:41,430
只是... 这全然是...
Only... it was...

359
00:22:43,300 --> 00:22:45,850
另外一种生活
another life.

360
00:22:47,250 --> 00:22:49,450
什么样的回忆?
What kind of memories?

361
00:22:52,540 --> 00:22:55,020
一架飞机失事了
There was a plane crash.

362
00:22:55,690 --> 00:22:57,640
接着...
And...

363
00:22:57,730 --> 00:23:00,080
我在一座岛上
I was on an island.

364
00:23:01,650 --> 00:23:03,420
我也在那儿?
And I was there?

365
00:23:03,420 --> 00:23:06,760
